  "id": "PLACE_the_ossuary_hollow",
  "label": "The Ossuary Hollow",
  "description": "The Ossuary Hollow is a deep cave cut into the rift-scarred flanks of Graveward Ridge, its entrance masked by a talus fan of vitrified scree and ash-cemented stones. Inside, angular basalt walls bear heat-glazed seams and impact scarring, recording centuries of particulate storms and high-energy fallout. A narrow floor trench channels meltless runoff and fine dust into stagnant basins, leaving the air metallic and dry under the ridge’s cold, veiled luminance. Sections of the ceiling have collapsed into buttressing pillars, shaping a labyrinthine interior suited to concealment and hard defense.",
